Wolf survived because a door opened in time.

Given a 0–10% chance of survival and facing a $13,000 emergency surgery estimate, Wolf's family was told the odds were against him. But they refused to give up. With the help of people who showed up when it mattered most, Wolf received the emergency care he needed.

His fight for survival revealed a painful reality — too many dogs are lost not because treatment doesn't exist, but because access to care doesn't. Wolf's story became the catalyst for everything The Wolf Project is building today.

## The Emergency

When Wolf's condition turned critical, time was running out. The estimate for emergency exploratory surgery was due upfront — after the family had already spent thousands on prior diagnostics. The barrier was not medicine. It was cost.

## The Fight

Wolf was given a 0–10% chance to survive. But treatment existed. And when access was made possible, Wolf fought back. He endured surgery, recovery, and every challenge in between — because someone made sure the door stayed open.

## The Mission

Wolf's story changed everything. It proved that when access to care exists, survival is possible. The Wolf Project was born from this moment — to make sure the next dog doesn't have to wait, and the next family doesn't have to face it alone.
